                                                            throws JPARSECException
        Creates a query to the USGS planetary map server.
        Parameters:
        targetBody - Target body, constants defined in class Target.TARGET, currently only Mars, the Moon, and Io are supported.
        width - Image width.
        height - image height.
        box - Box of bounding coordinates to display, in the form (west limit, south limit, east limit, north limit).
        dataset - Dataset id constant. Constants defined in this class. Set to null to use a default dataset.
        Returns:
        The query.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • getQueryToSiessModels

        public static java.lang.String getQueryToSiessModels(double metallicity,
                                     double Teff,
                                     double lum,
                                     double distanceModulus)
        Returns a query suitable for obtaining pre-main sequence star properties using Siess models.

        Reference:

        Siess et al. 1997, A&A 324, 556. Siess L., Dufour E., Forestini M. 2000, A&A, 358, 593.

        Parameters:
        metallicity - Star metallicity. Valid values are 0.01, 0.02, 0.03, and 0.04, being 0.02 the solar metallicity.
        Teff - Effective temperature in K.
        lum - Luminosity in solar units.
        distanceModulus - Distance modulus. 0 to avoid correcting extinction.
        Returns:
        The query.

      • getQueryToSDSS

        public static java.lang.String getQueryToSDSS(LocationElement loc,
                              GeneralQuery.SDSS_PLATE plate,
                              double field,
                              boolean fitsFormat)
                                       throws JPARSECException
        Deprecated. DSS queries can also be done using SkyView.
        Returns the query string for Sloan Digital Sky Survey.
        Parameters:
        loc - Equatorial location of the object.
        plate - plate type.
        field - field of view in arcminutes. From 0 to 60.0;
        fitsFormat - True to return a fits file, false for a gif one.
        Returns:
        The query.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If the input is invalid.

      • getQueryToSkyView

        public static java.lang.String getQueryToSkyView(java.lang.String name,
                                 GeneralQuery.SKYVIEW_SURVEY survey,
                                 double field,
                                 int width,
                                 boolean invert,
                                 boolean grid,
                                 GeneralQuery.SKYVIEW_COORDINATE scoord,
                                 GeneralQuery.SKYVIEW_PROJECTION sproj,
                                 GeneralQuery.SKYVIEW_LUT_TABLE slut,
                                 GeneralQuery.SKYVIEW_INTENSITY_SCALE sscale,
                                 java.lang.String catalog,
                                 java.lang.String contours)
                                          throws JPARSECException
        Returns the query string for SkyView.
        Parameters:
        name - Object name to be solved by Simbad or NED. You can also set as source the RA and DEC (2 values) in degrees.
        survey - Survey.
        field - Field of view in degrees.
        width - Width (or height, the same) of the image in pixels.
        invert - True to show inverted levels.
        grid - True to show the grid.
        scoord - Coordinate type. May be null (J2000).
        sproj - Projection type. May be null (TAN).
        slut - LUT color table. May be null (Gray image).
        sscale - Scale for the levels. May be null (Log).
        catalog - Name of one or several Vizier catalogs (separated by comma) to request and draw sources. Can be null.
        contours - Draw image contours from one survey on top of another. A value of the contour setting may comprise up to 5 colon separated fields. The first is the survey from which the contours are to be drawn. The second is the scaling of the contours, either 'Log', 'Sqrt' or 'Linear' (default Linear). The third value is the number of contours (default 4) which is followed by values for the first and last contours. One, two, three or all five values may be specified. More than one survey can be contoured by using comma as a separator. Example: 408mhz:Log:6:1:1000. Can be null.
        Returns:
        The query for a PNG image.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - if the name or the survey is null.
